1. CI/CD - Continuous Integration/ Continuous Deployment
Continuous integration (CI) automatically builds, tests, and integrates code changes within a shared repository; then.
Continuous delivery (CD) automatically delivers code changes to production-ready environments for approval; or.
Continuous deployment (CD) automatically deploys code changes to customers directly.

2. AWS - Amazon Web services
It is cloud platform that provides many services like Software as service, Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) and Platform as a Service (PaaS).
We can create Virtual machines as per our requirement. 

3. Git 
It is a open source software/tool that helps to maintain small to large projects that helps to track the changes in the repository.

4. Jenkins

